pronounce /prəˈnaʊns/

(pronouncing,pronounced,pronounces) 

1. V-T To pronounce a word means to say it using particular sounds. 发 (某字或词的) 音 

例： Have I pronounced your name correctly? 我把你的名字读对了吗？ 

2. V-T If you pronounce something to be true, you state that it is the case. 宣布 [正式] 

例： A specialist has now pronounced him fully fit. 一位专家已宣布他完全康复了。

